The paper proposes a novel approach to address the challenge of expensive computational cost and low learning efficiency in autoregressive networks. This makes it likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of autoregressive networks in sequence modeling tasks, which suggests that it could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses experiments on synthetic and real-world datasets, which could indicate that it belongs to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
